<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="325" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[136,787,1164,1284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">
<emphasis box="[174,393,1164,1188]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="325">Diagnostic characters.</emphasis>
– Opposite leaves, trimerous flowers with 3 or 6 two-locular stamens, staminodia of whorl III enlarged and conspicuous. Fruits enclosed in receptacle with scars of fallen tepals on top.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[174,602,1324,1348]" pageId="2" pageNumber="325" type="distribution">
